	abstract = {We present here a study on overlooked aspects of alternating current (AC) electrokinetics—AC electrophoretic (ACEP) phenomena. The dynamics of a particle with both polarizability and net charges in a non-uniform AC electric trapping ﬁeld is investigated. It is found that either electrophoretic (EP) or dielectrophoretic (DEP) effects can dominate the trapping dynamics, depending on experimental conditions. A dimensionless parameter γ is developed to predict the relative strength of EP and DEP effects in a quadrupole AC ﬁeld. An ACEP trap is feasible for charged particles in ‘salt-free’ or low salt concentration solutions. In contrast to DEP traps, an ACEP trap favors the downscaling of the particle size.},
